Class JDBCEvents

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--JDBCEvents
public class JDBCEvents
extends java.lang.Object

In general, this class (JDBCEvents) is the only class which can make connections to the Central Database (with the exception of IPS). Additionally, it handles button events.

See Also:
ExtensionFilter, IPS, SystemWindow

public void whenGetMyPortfolioDetailsPressed(javax.swing.JTable MyReturnedPortfolioTable,
                                             MPTSGlobalVariables systemWindowGlobalVariables)
This function is called when My Portfolio summary details are requested. Currently this function calculates three things:
  • Present Value of the portfolio
  • Total gain or loss of portfolio to date
  • Latest trade date

Parameters:
MyReturnedPortfolioTable - the My Portfolio table to be calculated
systemWindowGlobalVariables - global variables for interaction with the system

whenExecutionPressed

public void whenExecutionPressed(MPTSGlobalVariables systemWindowGlobalVariables)
This function is called when a trade execution is requested. I.e. a "buy" or "sell" request. Additionally, the function checks all inputted data to verify data integrity (returning and closing the function if a check was failed). If all checks have been passed, the function inserts the pending request into the Order Book.

Parameters:
systemWindowGlobalVariables - global variables for interaction with the system

initialiseAvailableSecurities

public java.lang.String[] initialiseAvailableSecurities()
This function initialises the entire list of available securities. This list of available securities is populated by accessing the data directly from the MPTS Central Database.

Returns:
an array of Strings which contain the security name
